1. New (Created)
The thread is created but not yet started.

Characteristics:
Thread object created
Resources allocated
Waiting to start execution

2. Ready (Runnable)
Thread is ready to execute and waiting for CPU time.

Characteristics:
Waiting in ready queue
Scheduler decides execution time

3. Running
Thread is currently executing on the CPU.

Characteristics:
Instructions are executed
Can move to waiting or terminated state

4. Blocked / Waiting
Thread is waiting for some resource or event.

Reasons:
Waiting for I/O
Waiting for lock
Waiting for signal

5. Terminated (Dead)
Thread has completed execution or stopped.

Characteristics:
Resources released
Cannot be executed again
